import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react"; import axios from "axios"; function Customer(props) { const[customerDetails, setCustomerDetails] = useState({}) useEffect(() => { getCustomerDetails(); }); const getCustomerDetails = () => { axios.get("http://localhost:8080/api/order/"+props.match.params.id).then((res) => { setCustomerDetails(res.data); }); const customer = { customerId: "45", name: "Md. jonayed bepari", companyName: "jonayedtech.Ltd", deliveryAddress: "Sumilpara, Adamjeee Nagar, Narayangonj", postalCode:"142", town:"Narayangonj", number:"01763039772", email:"mdjonayed@gamail.com", info:"Deliver Quiqly.." } setCustomerDetails(customer); }; return (
Customer Deatils
  • Customer Id :
    {customerDetails.customerId}
  • Name :
    {customerDetails.name}
  • Company Name (optional) :
    {customerDetails.companyName}
  • Delivery Address :
    {customerDetails.deliveryAddress}
  • Postal Code / Zip :
    {customerDetails.postalCode}
  • Town / City :
    {customerDetails.town}
  • Phone Number :
    {customerDetails.number}
  • Email Address :
    {customerDetails.email}
  • User Information :
    {customerDetails.info}
); } export default Customer;
